bubblewrap-bin packages the upstream "bubblewrap" project as a Python wheel.
The bundled `bwrap` binary is built from upstream sources and is licensed
under the GNU Lesser General Public License, version 2.0 or any later
version (LGPL-2.0-or-later).

The full LGPL-2.0 license text is available at:
  https://www.gnu.org/licenses/old-licenses/lgpl-2.0.html

Upstream project: https://github.com/containers/bubblewrap
Upstream license: LGPL-2.0-or-later (see upstream COPYING file).

The Python wrapper code in this package (under bubblewrap_bin/) is also
released under LGPL-2.0-or-later to match upstream.

Per LGPL section 6, the corresponding source for the bundled binary is
the upstream bubblewrap release whose version is recorded in
VENDORED_BWRAP_VERSION at the root of this distribution. That release is
publicly available from the upstream repository.
